<item>
            <title>[OAK-2642] DocumentNodeStore.dispose() may leave repository in an inconsistent state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2642</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The repository may become inconsistent when a commit happens while the DocumentNodeStore is disposed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The node store writes back pending _lastRevs and then unset the active flag in the clusterNodes collection. It is possible a commit gets through even after the _lastRevs had been updated and the active flag is cleared. This means the missing _lastRev updates will not be recovered on a restart or by another cluster node.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
